There are **5 tables** in the `public` schema, and **RLS is enabled on all of them** (each currently shows **0 rows**):

- `public.users` — PK: `id`; columns: `id`, `username`, `avatar_url`, `created_at`, `updated_at`.  
  FKs: `id → auth.users.id` (plus referenced by other tables).

- `public.stories` — PK: `id`; columns: `slug` (unique), `title`, `summary`, `created_by`, `created_at`, `updated_at`.  
  FK: `created_by → public.users.id`.

- `public.story_versions` — PK: `id`; columns include `story_id`, `outline` (jsonb), `status` enum (`draft|published`), `published_at`, `component_lock` (jsonb), `engine_range`, `shell` (jsonb), `theme`, timestamps.  
  FK: `story_id → public.stories.id`.

- `public.saves` — PK: `id`; columns: `story_id`, `user_id`, `save` (jsonb), `mode` (check: `solo|multiplayer`), timestamps.  
  FKs: `story_id → public.stories.id`, `user_id → public.users.id`.

- `public.multiplayer_sessions` — PK: `id`; columns: `story_version_id`, `host_id`, `title`, `status` enum (`pending|active|completed`), `settings` (jsonb), `session_state` (jsonb), `version` (int), timestamps.  
  FKs: `story_version_id → public.story_versions.id`, `host_id → public.users.id`.
